=Support Resources=

==SourceForge==

The principal location for getting assistance for ''ooRexx'' is
[http://www.sourceforge.net SourceForge]. It provides facilities for
[http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=684730&amp;group_id=119701&amp;func=browse reporting bugs],
[http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=684733&amp;group_id=119701&amp;func=browse feature requests],
[http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?atid=684731&amp;group_id=119701&amp;func=browse support requests] and
[http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=119701 file downloads].
<br />
See the [http://sourceforge.net/projects/oorexx ooRexx on SourceForge] page for all other support services provided.

==Mailing Lists==

To view the archives of the '''ooRexx''' mailing lists or to subscribe to them, visit
[http://sourceforge.net/mail/?group_id=119701 the ooRexx mailing lists list].
<br />
Another useful mailing list for expert advice on Object Rexx and Rexx in general is the
[http://www.rexxla.org/Members/ RexxLA Members] mailing list. This list is available only to
members of the
[http://www.rexxla.org/ Rexx Language Association].

==Newsgroups==

'''ooRexx''' does not have a dedicated newsgroup for discussions. but the generic newsgroup:
[news:comp.lang.rexx comp.lang.rexx] is an ideal place to obtain further information.

